{
  "texts": [
    "Third, agentic AI reshapes competitive dynamics in two-sided algorithmic markets.",
    "Here, both supply and demand can be orchestrated by AI, making tacit collusion more achievable through repeated, profit-driven interactions.",
    "While human consumers may be boundedly rational and less informed about products and prices, AI purchasing agents can optimize over longer horizons using data-driven insights.",
    "As a result, algorithms may naturally converge on pricing or resource allocations that stifle competition without direct coordination-underscoring the need for updated antitrust policies attuned to these digital realities.",
    "Finally, as agentic AI proliferates, the prospect of self-governing 'algorithmic societies' emerges."
  ]
}